    Final Fantasy Tactics 3d tile rasterizer

    Room
    [
        id,
        name,
        width,
        depth,
        height,
        water_height (0 = off),
        tiles,
        props
    ]

    Tiles
    [
        id,
        x,
        y,
        z,
        tex_top,
        tex_side,
        slope_type (slope type),
        type (0 = normal, 1 = water, 2 = damage etc)
    ]

    Props
    [
        x,
        y,
        z,
        type (prop, actor),
        sprite,
        data (agnostic)
    ]

    Grid based editor, 16x16 tile size

    move the cursor to a tile, click to paint
    scroll up/down to raise elevation
    change to slope to change its type
    change texture

    place props the same as tiles



    start with normal json
    byte encoded maps for quicker loads loater
    pak it after
    SANDBOX THE PAK'S



    Map list on the left
    Main editor window in the center
    Properties window on the right

    A = Select (Add tile/paint tile/Prop editor)
    X = Edit
    B = Cancel
    Y = Lower/raise

    LB/RB = Change Mode (Place, paint, delete)
